    "number": 2433,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "Fix: disable 2-CTA backward mode when block_sparse_tensors is used",
    "user": {
      "login": "jduprat",
      "id": 865537,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg2NTUzNw==",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/865537?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/jduprat",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jduprat/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "The SM100 2-CTA backward kernel does not properly handle block_sparse_tensors. When block sparsity is combined with 2-CTA mode, the kernel hits an assertion:\r\n  'AssertionError: 2-CTA mode does not support block sparsity'\r\n\r\nThis fix adds block_sparse_tensors to the disable_2cta condition in the backward path, forcing the 1-CTA kernel when block sparsity is active. The 1-CTA backward kernel already supports block_sparse_tensors correctly.\r\n\r\nWithout this fix, any backward pass using block_sparse_tensors on SM100 (B200/GB200) with head_dim >= 128 will crash with the above assertion.",
    "created_at": "2026-04-03T18:15:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-04-03T18:39:10Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-03T18:39:10Z",
